PREAMBLE
================================================================================

This license governs the use, reproduction, modification, and distribution of
the SAPTARA software framework ("the Software"), which is a web application
vulnerability assessment tool developed as an academic project. The purpose of
this license is to permit free use of the Software for academic, research, and
personal learning purposes while prohibiting commercial exploitation, misuse
against systems without authorisation, and redistribution without proper
attribution.

The authors believe that security research tools should be freely available to
the academic and security research community. At the same time, the authors
recognise that such tools carry inherent risks if misused and therefore impose
conditions designed to promote responsible and ethical use.

================================================================================
SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

1.1 "Software" means the SAPTARA source code, documentation, configuration
    files, scripts, and all associated materials distributed under this license.

1.2 "Contributor" means any individual or entity that has submitted code,
    documentation, or other materials to the Software.

1.3 "Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or derived from the
    Software, including modifications, translations, adaptations, or works that
    incorporate substantial portions of the Software.

1.4 "Authorised Target" means a system, application, or network that the user
    owns, operates, or has received explicit written permission from the owner
    to test.

1.5 "Commercial Use" means any use of the Software primarily intended for or
    directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation, including
    but not limited to offering the Software as a service, incorporating it
    into a commercial product, or using it to generate revenue.

1.6 "Academic Use" means use of the Software for non-commercial educational
    purposes, academic research, coursework, thesis work, or personal learning,
    where no monetary compensation is received for the use of the Software.

