SECTION 3 — RESTRICTIONS
================================================================================

The following uses are expressly prohibited:

3.1 UNAUTHORISED TESTING. You may not use the Software to test, probe, scan,
    or attack any system, application, network, or service that you do not own
    or for which you do not have explicit written authorisation from the owner.
    Unauthorised use of this Software against third-party systems may constitute
    a criminal offence under applicable law, including but not limited to the
    Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (United States), the Computer Misuse Act
    (United Kingdom), and equivalent legislation in other jurisdictions.

3.2 COMMERCIAL USE. You may not use the Software for Commercial Use without
    obtaining a separate commercial license from the copyright holders. This
    includes but is not limited to:
    (a) Offering the Software or its functionality as a paid service;
    (b) Incorporating the Software into a commercial security product;
    (c) Using the Software to perform paid penetration testing engagements
        without a commercial license;
    (d) Selling, licensing, or sublicensing the Software for monetary
        compensation.

3.3 MALICIOUS USE. You may not use the Software to:
    (a) Gain unauthorised access to any computer system or network;
    (b) Disrupt, damage, or degrade the availability of any service;
    (c) Steal, exfiltrate, or compromise personal data or confidential
        information;
    (d) Facilitate any activity that violates applicable law.

3.4 MISREPRESENTATION. You may not remove or alter copyright notices, license
    terms, or attribution statements from the Software or any Derivative Work.
    You may not represent the Software as your own original work without
    acknowledging the original authors.

3.5 PATENT USE. This license does not grant any rights to use any patent claims
    of any Contributor. If you institute patent litigation against any entity
    alleging that the Software infringes a patent, your rights under this
    license terminate automatically.

================================================================================
SECTION 4 — ETHICAL USE REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

4.1 AUTHORISATION REQUIREMENT. Before using the Software against any target,
    you must obtain and retain written authorisation from the owner of that
    target. This authorisation must specify the scope of testing permitted,
    the time period during which testing is authorised, and the contact
    information of the authorising party.

4.2 RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE. If you discover a vulnerability in a third-party
    system while using the Software under authorised testing, you are encouraged
    to follow responsible disclosure practices by notifying the affected
    organisation privately and allowing a reasonable period for remediation
    before public disclosure.

4.3 DATA HANDLING. Any sensitive data, credentials, or personal information
    discovered during authorised testing must be handled in accordance with
    applicable data protection laws and the terms of your testing authorisation.
    Such data must not be retained beyond the period necessary for the testing
    engagement.

4.4 SCOPE LIMITATION. You must not exceed the scope of your testing
    authorisation. If your authorisation covers specific systems or endpoints,
    you must not use the Software to test systems or endpoints outside that
    scope.

